# Navbar (site-wide)

The primary navigation is **one shared component** used on every page. Behaviour and markup must stay consistent everywhere.

## Source of truth

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/components/Navbar/` | Component module (`Navbar.jsx`, `NavLinksList.jsx`, `navLinks.js`, `useNavbarScroll.js`) |
| `src/components/NavLink.jsx` | Terminal-style link + typing interaction |
| `styles/components/navbar.css` | Layout, compact notch, mobile drawer |
| `src/motion/presets.js` | `navbarMorphTransition`, `navbarBrandMotion`, `navbarShellMotion`, mobile nav variants |

## Mounting

- Import only from `src/components/Navbar` (barrel).
- Render **once** in `App.jsx` above `<main>` — never duplicate `<Navbar />` or reimplement header markup inside page sections.
- New routes/pages must not add their own header, logo row, or nav list.

## Locked behaviour

### Desktop (≥ 810px)

- Default: full-width header — logo left, inline nav links right.
- Scroll down past ~96px: morphs to a **centred compact notch** (logo + links), eased layout + subtle logo blur.
- Scroll back to the top: returns to full header (scrolling up alone does not expand).
- No hamburger on desktop.

### Mobile (< 810px)

- **No compact scroll morph** — header stays full width at all scroll positions.
- Hamburger opens a **full-height drawer** (`site-nav--drawer`) below the header bar, with backdrop.
- Drawer and backdrop are **siblings of `<header>`** inside `site-header-shell`, not children of the animated header (fixed positioning must not sit inside transformed/filtered ancestors).

### All viewports

- Links defined only in `navLinks.js` (Projects, Playground, Notes, About).
- `body.is-nav-menu-open` locks scroll when mobile menu is open.
- Escape closes mobile menu.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` via existing motion presets.

## Do not

- Add per-page nav markup or alternate headers.
- Nest mobile `position: fixed` menu panels inside `motion` elements that use `layout`, `filter`, or blur on ancestors.
- Enable compact scroll state on mobile.
- Change nav link set in page files — update `navLinks.js` only.
- Move navbar styles into page CSS (`homepage.css`, etc.) — keep chrome in `styles/components/navbar.css`.

## Changing the navbar

If a task asks to change nav behaviour, links, or chrome: edit the Navbar module and `navbar.css` together, then verify desktop scroll morph and mobile drawer on a long page.
